<darkcolour>A6416E</darkcolour><section><title>Past Simple questions</title><sectiontitle>Use &lt;I&gt;did&lt;/I&gt; + verb to make questions in the Past Simple.</sectiontitle><titlesound>ELEMGRAM_6_2_1.mp3</titlesound><text1>Marilyn &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;stayed&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; at home last night.</text1><sound1>ELEMGRAM_6_2_2.mp3</sound1><text1a>&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;Did Marilyn stay&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; at home last night?</text1a><text2>We &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;finished&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; work at 3 o'clock.</text2><sound2>ELEMGRAM_6_2_3.mp3</sound2><text2a>When &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;did we finish&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; work?</text2a><titlesound2>ELEMGRAM_6_2_4.mp3</titlesound2><sectiontitle2>Use &lt;I&gt;did&lt;/I&gt; or &lt;I&gt;didn't&lt;/I&gt; to make short answers.</sectiontitle2><text3>&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;Did you study &lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;at university?</text3><sound3>ELEMGRAM_6_2_5.mp3</sound3><text3a>Yes, &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;I did&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;. / No, &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;I didn't.&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;</text3a><text4>&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;Did they remember&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; the drinks?</text4><sound4>ELEMGRAM_6_2_6.mp3</sound4><text4a>Yes, &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;they did&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;. / No, &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;they didn't.&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;</text4a></section></grammar>